WEBVTT

00:00.701 --> 00:04.737
[ static ]

00:04.739 --> 00:09.941
♪ my dreams are all dead
and buried ♪

00:09.943 --> 00:14.079
♪ sometimes I wish the sun
would just explode ♪

00:15.166 --> 00:20.085
♪ when god comes
and calls me to his kingdom ♪

00:20.087 --> 00:24.456
♪ I'll take all
you sons of bitches when I go ♪

00:24.458 --> 00:27.493
♪ let her blow-oh-oh-oh-oh ♪

00:27.495 --> 00:28.660
my turn.

00:28.662 --> 00:29.962
Hell no.
Hey, man, let me drive

00:29.964 --> 00:32.264
that thing, come on!
Do not touch the trim!

00:34.969 --> 00:37.569
I'm so glad you could fit
this date in during my break.

00:37.571 --> 00:39.488
Oh, thank you.

00:39.490 --> 00:41.306
Yeah, it's tough
being single,

00:41.308 --> 00:42.491
especially in this town.

00:42.493 --> 00:43.575
I'm ngle.

00:43.577 --> 00:45.611
Leroy, roll along.

00:45.613 --> 00:48.664
Tammi, I like this vibe
'tween you and me.

00:48.666 --> 00:51.316
But what's the deal
with you and mr. Squid?

00:51.318 --> 00:52.701
Oh, rusty?

00:52.703 --> 00:54.787
It's nothing romantic.
You know, we're friends.

00:54.789 --> 00:57.623
We have a child,
and we're raising him together.

00:57.625 --> 00:59.157
Weird.

00:59.159 --> 01:01.009
'cause here's you and him,
canoodling by the claw machine.

01:01.011 --> 01:02.928
Grabbing more than stuffies,
from what I can tell.

01:02.930 --> 01:05.464
You have this on your phone?
Oh, so I'm the stalker?

01:05.466 --> 01:06.598
Is that what you're saying?

01:06.600 --> 01:08.517
Look, it's our first date.

01:08.519 --> 01:10.018
Please don't be
another psycho.

01:10.020 --> 01:12.170
This right here
ain't happening.

01:12.172 --> 01:16.525
You're under 30, right?
I won't date anyone over 30.

01:17.745 --> 01:19.211
Rusty: You're moving?
To elberton?

01:19.213 --> 01:20.813
That's exactly
what I'm doing,

01:20.815 --> 01:23.014
'cause there is<i> nothing</i> for me
in this town.

01:23.016 --> 01:25.484
W-what about macho man?
What about his education?

01:25.486 --> 01:27.286
Elberton has
better schools.

01:27.288 --> 01:28.520
Look at randy's homework.

01:28.522 --> 01:30.456
He's still making
hand turkeys...

01:30.458 --> 01:31.490
That looks fine to me.

01:31.492 --> 01:32.708
...In math.

01:32.710 --> 01:34.743
What about me?
What about us?

01:34.745 --> 01:36.628
Why don't you just
move down there with us?

01:36.630 --> 01:38.413
I mean, well,
maybe I wi--

01:38.415 --> 01:41.884
well, I mean, I could,
but tammi, granny needs me.

01:41.886 --> 01:43.702
You need your
grandma's permission

01:43.704 --> 01:45.137
to live your own life?

01:45.139 --> 01:48.206
Let me guess what the purple
old raisin's gonna say.

01:48.208 --> 01:52.210
Elberton is just people
with different colors of skin

01:52.212 --> 01:55.848
making fun of you in languages
you don't understand.

01:55.850 --> 01:58.901
Now, I know you got your
own life to live, rusty,

01:58.903 --> 02:02.488
and you should have to
live it here and take care of me

02:02.490 --> 02:07.609
like I had to with my kinfolk
until I was too old to escape.

02:07.611 --> 02:10.445
There's only two ways
out of this house --

02:10.447 --> 02:13.415
in handcuffs
or in a c-coffin.

02:13.417 --> 02:14.700
Granny? You okay?

02:14.702 --> 02:17.836
Ah, she's just
playing possum.

02:17.838 --> 02:19.755
Though usually she say
some version of "ow"

02:19.757 --> 02:21.590
when I do that.

02:21.592 --> 02:23.909
Oh, no!
Call 911!

02:23.911 --> 02:26.512
911! 911!
911!

02:26.514 --> 02:28.413
911!
911!

02:28.415 --> 02:32.017
[ sobbing ]

02:32.019 --> 02:34.085
I can't believe
she's gone.

02:34.087 --> 02:36.605
I only wish I could
go back in time

02:36.607 --> 02:38.190
and have her
move her shit out

02:38.192 --> 02:40.526
so I didn't have to
do that now!

02:40.528 --> 02:42.928
[ sobs ]
oh, is that the will?

02:42.930 --> 02:44.730
It does say "will...

02:44.732 --> 02:47.149
You please destroy
my porno stash

02:47.151 --> 02:49.768
so my family
don't find out."

02:49.770 --> 02:51.937
ooh, I-I don't think
she meant for me

02:51.939 --> 02:53.455
to read that out loud.

02:53.457 --> 02:55.791
Was this
her wedding ring?

02:55.793 --> 02:58.627
Yep.
Now that she's gone,

02:58.629 --> 03:01.446
I think it'd look pretty snazzy
on my finger, don't you think?

03:01.448 --> 03:03.966
You know, maybe that oughta
be buried with granny.

03:03.968 --> 03:06.635
Yeah, daddy, I-I think
it just looks a little...

03:06.637 --> 03:08.170
Feminine.
It's a woman's ring-

03:08.172 --> 03:09.955
I can't<i> believe</i>
you'd suggest

03:09.957 --> 03:12.558
I wear a ladies' ring
to elevate my status.

03:12.560 --> 03:15.894
Granny should be buried
with this, her wolfman mask,

03:15.896 --> 03:17.980
and all her other
earthly treasures.

03:17.982 --> 03:19.648
Now, box all this shit up.

03:19.650 --> 03:22.467
I want it out of here
by noon today!

03:22.469 --> 03:23.969
[ somber music plays ]

03:23.971 --> 03:25.737
granny was not
no damn wolfman.

03:25.739 --> 03:28.156
Not a very convincing one.

03:28.158 --> 03:29.241
She's gone.

03:29.243 --> 03:30.993
Move to elberton
with us, rusty.

03:30.995 --> 03:32.444
You're moving to elberton?

03:32.446 --> 03:35.080
My god, elberton will eat
you alive, tammi.

03:35.082 --> 03:37.866
And now that they've got
that granite museum up there,

03:37.868 --> 03:39.618
it's just nothing
but a tourist trap.

03:39.620 --> 03:41.336
Why you run off
and move to elberton?

03:41.338 --> 03:43.505
Can you please
not broadcast that?

03:43.507 --> 03:46.458
Then I guess we'll
<i> podcast</i> it, tammi.

03:46.460 --> 03:49.678
That's right -- me and denny
are starting a podcast,

03:49.680 --> 03:52.347
just like in the "big city"
of elberton.

03:52.349 --> 03:54.433
And we're calling it
"tater talk."

03:54.435 --> 03:55.884
name to be decided.

03:55.886 --> 03:57.469
I've already printed
the koozies, denny.

03:57.471 --> 03:59.104
They'll think we're talking
about potatoes.

03:59.106 --> 04:01.006
It's got alliteration.
It's folksy.

04:01.008 --> 04:02.224
What's not to like?

04:02.226 --> 04:03.725
I'm sure I'll be able
to download

04:03.727 --> 04:05.027
your podcast
from elberton.

04:05.029 --> 04:07.195
I hate to mansplain to you,
tammi,

04:07.197 --> 04:09.231
but that's not
how podcasts work.

04:09.233 --> 04:10.782
Would either of y'all
be interested

04:10.784 --> 04:12.317
in being interviewed
for a podcast?

04:12.319 --> 04:13.852
I was gonna ask, denny.

04:13.854 --> 04:16.622
It should come from me,
the main host.

04:16.624 --> 04:18.757
[ somber music playing ]

04:18.759 --> 04:20.692
♪

04:20.694 --> 04:22.628
[ bell tolls ]

04:22.630 --> 04:24.830
oh!
I'm coming, lord!

04:24.832 --> 04:26.364
About damn time!
Aah!

04:26.366 --> 04:28.583
Why didn't you die when you
was young and pretty?

04:28.585 --> 04:30.719
Oh, no.
Ugh.

04:30.721 --> 04:32.587
Maybe put that mask
back on.

04:32.589 --> 04:33.805
Where's jesus?!

04:33.807 --> 04:35.373
Oh, well.

04:35.375 --> 04:38.010
I settled for you once.
I can settle for you again.

04:38.012 --> 04:39.678
Now, fry me up some eggs.

04:39.680 --> 04:42.714
I'll die 1,000 times before
I fry any eggs for your ass!

04:42.716 --> 04:44.066
[ chuckles ]
oh, easy now.

04:44.068 --> 04:46.268
Are we not doing this
closed casket?

04:46.270 --> 04:48.219
Seriously? Okay.

04:48.221 --> 04:51.690
Uh, what can I say about
ruby jean cuyler

04:51.692 --> 04:53.358
that won't offend?

04:53.360 --> 04:54.860
Read this!

04:54.862 --> 04:56.361
I spent all night
on it.

04:56.363 --> 04:57.395
[ sighs ]

04:57.397 --> 05:00.899
now presenting a man
you can't scare,

05:00.901 --> 05:02.417
the walking nightmare.

05:02.419 --> 05:05.570
The women want his body
and the men want his hair.

05:05.572 --> 05:09.341
Introducing the one and only,
the never lonely,

05:09.343 --> 05:12.311
early "the diamond child"
cuyler.

05:12.313 --> 05:14.212
Now do
the ric flair whoo.

05:14.214 --> 05:17.049
-No, I don't think so.
-Whoo!

05:17.051 --> 05:18.850
How y'all doin' out there?!

05:18.852 --> 05:21.019
I hope all y'all
can respect my privacy

05:21.021 --> 05:23.855
by giving up for me
during this painful time!

05:23.857 --> 05:25.724
Come on, let's hear it!

05:25.726 --> 05:27.609
All the way
from the back!

05:27.611 --> 05:29.277
[ whooshing ]

05:29.279 --> 05:31.480
hey, the show's
down here, folks.

05:31.482 --> 05:33.865
Now, people have asked me,
"diamond child,

05:33.867 --> 05:35.867
why would you bury
you momma in a ring

05:35.869 --> 05:38.153
that looks so good --
<i> so</i> good --

05:38.155 --> 05:40.939
on your own finger?
[ camera shutter clicks ]

05:40.941 --> 05:42.124
sheriff: That's a woman's ring,
isn't it?

05:42.126 --> 05:43.458
And that's
what I told them.

05:43.460 --> 05:46.628
It's a women's ring,
and it belongs on a woman.

05:46.630 --> 05:47.946
Goodbye, momma.

05:47.948 --> 05:49.915
You'll always be
the wolfman to me.

05:49.917 --> 05:50.966
[ sobs ]

05:50.968 --> 05:54.336
[ howls and cries ]

05:54.338 --> 05:57.389
[ sobs ]

05:57.391 --> 05:58.957
w-where you going?
What's the rush?

05:58.959 --> 06:00.142
We gotta pack.

06:00.144 --> 06:01.476
Are you coming with us
or not?

06:01.478 --> 06:03.812
I mean, I would, but daddy
just lost his momma.

06:03.814 --> 06:05.230
And he needs me
right now.

06:05.232 --> 06:06.982
And just how much time
does<i> he</i> need?

06:06.984 --> 06:08.483
I'm an orphan!

06:08.485 --> 06:10.301
[ wails and sobs ]

06:10.303 --> 06:11.353
I don't know.

06:11.355 --> 06:13.071
Just until he gets old
and passes on maybe?

06:13.073 --> 06:14.906
These ain't obstacles
to moving, rusty.

06:14.908 --> 06:16.358
They're excuses.

06:16.360 --> 06:18.410
So go comfort your daddy
for the rest of your life,

06:18.412 --> 06:19.995
and I'll text you
our new address.

06:19.997 --> 06:21.446
Aw, don't be that way.

06:21.448 --> 06:22.781
Tammi! Randy!

06:22.783 --> 06:24.983
Early: [ echoing ]
boo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

06:24.985 --> 06:26.551
I know, daddy.
I'm here.

06:26.553 --> 06:27.736
It's gonna be alright.

06:27.738 --> 06:29.771
I know it is.
Finally!

06:29.773 --> 06:32.274
I'm the one on top of
this ponzi scheme.

06:32.276 --> 06:33.391
Ponzi scheme?

06:33.393 --> 06:36.027
Well, it's more
of a marketing pyramid.

06:36.029 --> 06:37.829
Granny waited for her dad
to die.

06:37.831 --> 06:39.281
I waited on her to die.

06:39.283 --> 06:41.500
And now you get to
wait on me,

06:41.502 --> 06:42.868
hand and foot.

06:42.870 --> 06:44.336
Where's your young'un?

06:44.338 --> 06:45.887
Early: You better get an intern
in this program.

06:45.889 --> 06:48.173
He's moving with tammi
to elberton.

06:48.175 --> 06:50.125
There's only two ways
out of this house.

06:50.127 --> 06:51.760
In handcuffs
or in a coffin.

06:51.762 --> 06:53.762
He gets it.
Grab your shovel, boy.

06:53.764 --> 06:55.847
I got me
a business proposition,

06:55.849 --> 06:57.432
and it is shovel-ready.

06:58.302 --> 07:00.635
Please tell me we ain't
digging up granny's body.

07:00.637 --> 07:01.970
Not all of it.

07:01.972 --> 07:04.189
Just the part wearing that
costly unisexual ring,

07:04.191 --> 07:06.141
for men<i> and</i> for women.

07:06.143 --> 07:07.809
She ain't gonna need it
where she's going.

07:07.811 --> 07:09.194
But you told sheriff --

07:09.196 --> 07:12.280
don't you "you-said
I-said what-did-I-say" me.

07:12.282 --> 07:16.234
♪

07:16.236 --> 07:17.536
[ chuckles ]

07:17.538 --> 07:19.037
my precocious.

07:19.039 --> 07:20.939
That ring
stays with granny.

07:20.941 --> 07:22.240
I'm the head
of this cult now,

07:22.242 --> 07:23.742
and<i> I</i> call the shots!

07:23.744 --> 07:25.577
I did not stay
in dougal county

07:25.579 --> 07:28.463
to be part of no family
pyramid-scheme guilt cult.

07:28.465 --> 07:30.949
Then there's only one way
to settle this.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.083
Spades up!

07:32.085 --> 07:33.385
Daddy, don't make me
hurt you.

07:33.387 --> 07:35.954
I don't want to do this.
The ring is mine!

07:35.956 --> 07:37.222
[ clang! ]

07:37.224 --> 07:39.057
the ring is<i> mine!</i>

07:39.059 --> 07:41.510
Granny?
Is that really you?

07:41.512 --> 07:42.961
Yeah, as you can see,

07:42.963 --> 07:45.931
I didn't make it
to the jesus meet-and-greet.

07:45.933 --> 07:48.099
Pearly gates,
eternal salvation --

07:48.101 --> 07:50.635
all of it's just
a damn bait-and-switch.

07:50.637 --> 07:54.472
That's why you need to get
<i> yours</i> while you're still alive.

07:54.474 --> 07:55.907
[ early groans ]

07:55.909 --> 07:58.410
you mind
if I borrow your ring?

07:58.412 --> 07:59.945
You know, rusty,

07:59.947 --> 08:02.447
I never did
like tammi but...

08:04.585 --> 08:07.252
...There's no second part
to that sentence.

08:07.254 --> 08:09.287
Didn't like the woman.
Not a fan.

08:09.289 --> 08:10.505
Thank you, granny.
I...

08:10.507 --> 08:11.873
I'll take that
as your blessing.

08:11.875 --> 08:13.175
Oh, you're taking
his truck?

08:13.177 --> 08:15.544
Oh, you got some real balls now,
don't ya?

08:15.546 --> 08:16.928
[ engine starts ]

08:16.930 --> 08:19.464
I might be seeing you
sooner than I thought.

08:20.350 --> 08:22.184
I want you to marry me,
tammi,

08:22.186 --> 08:24.168
and I want to move
with y'all to elberton.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.770
Don't play with me,
rusty,

08:25.772 --> 08:27.138
unless you're serious.

08:28.392 --> 08:30.525
Holy shit.
You<i> are</i> serious.

08:30.527 --> 08:32.510
Ooh, early is gonna
raise some hell

08:32.512 --> 08:34.345
when he figures out
one of his trucks is missing.

08:34.347 --> 08:37.065
Yeah, I-I stole it.
We need to get.

08:37.067 --> 08:39.234
Early, have you tried
calling rusty?

08:39.236 --> 08:41.319
Maybe he's just borrowed
the truck for a little bit.

08:41.321 --> 08:43.071
He stole
granny's ring, too.

08:43.073 --> 08:45.957
Put out an apb on a man
wearing a woman's ring.

08:45.959 --> 08:47.492
Thinking he can
pull that off.

08:47.494 --> 08:48.960
The audacity!

08:48.962 --> 08:51.796
[ vehicle approaching ]

08:51.798 --> 08:53.832
oh, here we go.

08:53.834 --> 08:54.883
Pull it over!

08:54.885 --> 08:56.200
Off to the side!

08:56.202 --> 08:57.769
The jig is up!
[ cocks gun ]

08:57.771 --> 09:00.171
rusty, you know he ain't gonna
let us cross the county line.

09:00.173 --> 09:01.840
Well, it ain't
his decision.

09:01.842 --> 09:03.058
Fasten your seat belt.

09:03.060 --> 09:05.710
Well, damn.
It's about time.

09:05.712 --> 09:08.263
[ engine revving ]

09:08.265 --> 09:09.881
he ain't gonna do it.

09:09.883 --> 09:11.549
[ tires squeal ]
I think
he<i> is</i> gonna do it!

09:11.551 --> 09:13.485
He's definitely doing it.
Get out of the way, early!

09:13.487 --> 09:14.402
Agh!

09:14.404 --> 09:15.954
[ screams ]
sorry, daddy.

09:15.956 --> 09:17.489
But I want randy
to have all the things

09:17.491 --> 09:18.890
I didn't have.

09:18.892 --> 09:21.192
And I want you<i> not</i> to have
the things I didn't have.

09:21.194 --> 09:23.995
That's a sacrifice
we all have to make!

09:23.997 --> 09:26.114
[ tires screech ]
aaaah!

09:28.902 --> 09:30.535
[ grunts ]
sorry, daddy.

09:30.537 --> 09:32.804
Maybe we'll, uh, see you
at thanksgiving or something.

09:32.806 --> 09:34.422
Tammi:
Don't count on it!

09:34.424 --> 09:36.608
Whoo-hoo!
Goodbye, dougal county!

09:36.610 --> 09:39.311
Well, should we
do something?
[ siren wailing ]

09:39.313 --> 09:41.179
we<i> are</i> doing something,
denny.

09:41.181 --> 09:43.298
[ siren stops ]
we're letting rusty
and his family have a life.

09:43.300 --> 09:44.849
They're getting away!

09:44.851 --> 09:47.135
Call in a air strike
from the jewish space lasers!

09:47.137 --> 09:49.304
[ clang! ]
d'ah!

09:49.306 --> 09:52.807
Huh, usually he says some
version of "ow" when I do that.

09:52.809 --> 09:55.610
Let me knock the stuffing
out of him one time.

09:55.612 --> 09:58.429
Okay, but don't hit him
<i> too</i> hard.

09:58.431 --> 10:00.398
We don't want him
up here with us.

10:00.400 --> 10:01.232
[ clang! ]

10:01.234 --> 10:03.368
you said "us."

10:03.370 --> 10:05.654
let's wail on him
together. Uh!

10:05.656 --> 10:09.240
You know -- ugh! --
Ghosts can't get pregnant.

10:09.242 --> 10:11.326
But who says
we shouldn't try?

10:11.328 --> 10:14.112
Oh, you!
[ laughs ]

10:14.114 --> 10:15.330
[ clang! ]

10:15.332 --> 10:18.583
ruby jean, rest in peace,
sweetie.

10:18.585 --> 10:22.387
Narrator:
And so rusty moved with tammi
and macho man to elberton,

10:22.389 --> 10:27.058
thus hopefully breaking
the cycle of poverty and abuse.

10:27.060 --> 10:29.177
Early would swear
to exact his revenge,

10:29.179 --> 10:31.429
but like many things
in early's life,

10:31.431 --> 10:33.098
he never followed through,

10:33.100 --> 10:36.101
deeming elberton too close
to the edge of the flat earth

10:36.103 --> 10:38.186
and not worth
scaling an ice wall

10:38.188 --> 10:40.271
to tangle with dragons.

10:40.273 --> 10:43.942
This show...
Was called "squidbillies."

10:43.944 --> 10:51.616
♪

10:51.618 --> 10:59.057
♪

10:59.059 --> 11:06.297
♪
